Notes: Although 'row_id' is an identifier, it is not directly mapped through the ontology paths; here, it is associated with the main entity for identification purposes.
The 'patient_id' directly relates to the Patient entity, making Path 1 the most semantically appropriate to link measurements to patients.
Measurement codes are best represented via the 'hasCode' property linking to a Code entity, capturing the coded nature of the measurement.
The measurement value logically maps to a Quantity entity, representing the measured amount with potential units.
Units complement the measurement value, providing context, thus linked via 'hasQuantity'.
Measurement date is a DateTime datatype, directly mapped to the 'hasMeasurementDateTime' property for precise temporal data.
